  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/riveron/2dc14c20-5d31-4f80-a643-44f42ac6d611/application",
    "company": "Riveron",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "4e26cf3db1accb5c",
    "department": "Client Service",
    "description": "When you join the Valuation Services group within our Financial Advisory (FA) segment, you will be part of a team working hand-in-hand with our clients to develop complex financial models to determine the fair value of various business interests and assets. Our group partners with clients to navigate strategic business initiatives and financial reporting matters associated with transformative business growth or events – such as a carve-out, IPO, merger and acquisitions. At its core, the work we do in FA is driven by change, which means the projects are dynamic in nature and the impact of your work will be highly visible.\n\nAs a Manager, you will lead the delivery of client engagements, serving as the day-to-day point of contact for the client, guiding junior consultants through the project lifecycle, and ensuring high quality projects are consistently executed on time and on budget. While developing your project and people management skills, you will further augment your advisory toolkit by digging deep into client problems in real-time and delivering ongoing thought partnership. We expect Managers to own workstreams and projects, interface directly with senior client executives, and develop tailored deliverables. With experienced leaders to guide you along the way – including a dedicated performance advisor – we are invested in accelerating your growth.\n\nWho You Are:\n\n - Bachelor’s or Master’s in Finance, Accounting, or related field of study\n\n - Minimum 5 years of experience in valuation analyses for financial reporting purposes as well as tax purposes\n\n - Have or obtaining a CFA, ASA, or CEIV credential\n\n - Extensive knowledge of Microsoft Office Excel\n\n - Experience with valuation concepts and approaches (income, market and cost) utilized to value: business enterprise/equity valuations, intangible assets, contingent consideration, and complex securities and debt instruments\n\n - You have a passion for sustaining long-term client relationships\n\n - You are skilled at leading and developing teams and individuals\n\n - You thrive in an ever-changing, dynamic work environment\n\n - You readily identify problems and instinctively look for solutions\n\n - You believe that exceeding client expectations and having fun at work are mutually dependent\n\n - You enjoy participating in internal and external company initiatives such as community service, training, recruiting, committees, conference panels, and firm events\n\nWhat You'll Do:\n\n - Assist with projects which will include valuations for the following: business enterprise/equity valuations, intellectual property/intangible assets, impairment testing – goodwill and long-lived assets, contingent consideration, and stock options, complex securities, and debt instruments.\n\n - Directly engage with client management and their advisors to gain an understanding of their operations, processes, and strategic objectives\n\n - Prepare analyses for financial reporting, tax, and general consulting purposes\n\n - Develop financial models and analyze data in complex spreadsheets\n\n - Prepare narrative business valuation reports to be shared with the client as a deliverable\n\n - Perform industry research and competitive analysis\n\nAbout Riveron:\n\nAt Riveron, we partner with clients—from global multinationals to high-growth private entities—to solve complex finance challenges, guided by our DELTA values: Drive, Excellence, Leadership, Teamwork, and Accountability. Our entrepreneurial culture thrives on collaboration, diverse perspectives, and delivering exceptional outcomes. We are committed to fostering growth, both for our clients and our people, through mentorship, integrity, and a client-centric approach. This inclusive environment offers flexibility, progressive benefits, and meaningful opportunities for impactful work that supports well-being in and out of the office.\n\nCheck us out on social media:\n\nLinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/company/riveron/life/culture/ Glassdoor https://www.glassdoor.com/Photos/Riveron-Office-Photos-E672242.htm Instagram https://www.instagram.com/riveronconsulting/ Facebook https://www.facebook.com/RiveronConsulting/\n\nRiveron Consulting is an Equal Opportunity Employer and believes that we are stronger together through our diversity. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, age, national origin, disability status, protected veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or any other characteristic protected by law.\n\nFull time roles are eligible for a full range of benefits including medical, dental, and vision insurance, 401(k) with company match, and PTO. A complete description of all available benefits can be found at Riveron's Benefits page at https://riveron.com/riveron-life/. Contract roles are not eligible for benefits.\n\n\nFRAUD ALERT\n\nPlease beware of fraudulent schemes or impersonations when going through the job application process. A Riveron employee will never recruit via text or extend unsolicited employment offers. Additionally, a Riveron employee will never ask you to exchange money or purchase anything as part of the recruiting process.\n\n\nWE MAY USE ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE (AI) TOOLS TO SUPPORT PARTS OF THE HIRING PROCESS, SUCH AS REVIEWING APPLICATIONS, ANALYZING RESUMES, OR ASSESSING RESPONSES. THESE TOOLS ASSIST OUR RECRUITMENT TEAM BUT DO NOT REPLACE HUMAN JUDGMENT. FINAL HIRING DECISIONS ARE ULTIMATELY MADE BY HUMANS. IF YOU WOULD LIKE MORE INFORMATION ABOUT HOW YOUR DATA IS PROCESSED, PLEASE CONTACT US.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
